understand what the route uses)\n4. `package.json` (to find lint/typecheck/build/test commands)\n\n## Step 2: Run Phase A checks\n\nRun each check and capture exact output:\n\n1. **File check**: Verify `src/app/api/events/route.ts` exists and contains `export.*POST` or `export async function POST`\n2. **Test suite**: Run `pnpm test` from the project root, capture output including pass/fail counts. Note: some tests may be skipped (that's expected).\n3. **Lint check**: First run `pnpm lint --write` (Biome auto-fix), then run `pnpm lint` in check mode. Capture exit code and output.\n4. **Type check**: Run `pnpm typecheck`. Capture exit code and any errors.\n5. **Build check**: Run `pnpm build`. Capture exit code. If it fails, capture the errors.\n\n**If any Phase A check fails**: record results, do NOT proceed to Phase B (integration HTTP checks). Write the eval file with NEEDS_WORK.\n\n## Step 3: If all Phase A pass, run Phase B (integration gap checks)\n\nThe integration gap tests require a running dev server AND a running ClickHouse instance. \n\nFirst check if ClickHouse is already running:\n```bash\ncurl -s http://localhost:8123/ping\n```\n\nIf ClickHouse is not running, note that integration tests cannot be run without it. Mark integration gap criteria as \"❌ (ClickHouse not running)\" but do NOT fail the score for infrastructure reasons.\n\nIf ClickHouse IS running:\n1. Check if dev server is running: `curl -s http://localhost:3000`\n2. If not running, start it: `pnpm dev & DEV_PID=$!` and wait for it to be ready\n3. Run the integration tests\n4. Kill the dev server after: `kill $DEV_PID 2>/dev/null; kill $(lsof -ti:3000) 2>/dev/null; true`\n\n## Step 4: Write integration test file\n\nWrite integration HTTP tests in `src/app/api/events/__tests__/route.integration.test.ts` that cover the 3 integration gap criteria. These tests should:\n- Be clearly marked as requiring a running server (skip with a message if server not available, using a beforeAll check)\n- Use fetch() to hit http://localhost:3000/api/events\n- Check status codes and response body\n\nOnly write these if the Phase A checks pass. The tests should be written regardless of whether the server is currently running (they'll run in CI later when server is available).\n\n## Step 5: Write the eval file\n\nWrite `features/F5-eval-1.md` with:\n```markdown\n# F5 Eval Sprint 1 — 2026-04-15\n\n## Tests written\n\n- src/app/api/events/__tests__/route.integration.test.ts — covers 3 integration gap criteria (valid POST → 201, missing event_name → 400, missing identifiers → 400)\n\n## Sprint contract results\n| Criterion | Expected | Actual | Pass |\n|-----------|----------|--------|------|\n| File route.ts exists with POST export | exists | (actual) | ✅/❌ |\n| Test suite 0 failures | 0 failures | X failures | ✅/❌ |\n| Lint check | exit 0 | exit X | ✅/❌ |\n| Type check | exit 0 | exit X | ✅/❌ |\n| Build check | exit 0 | exit X | ✅/❌ |\n| Integration: valid POST → 201 | 201 + event_id + event_name | (actual) | ✅/❌/— |\n| Integration: missing event_name → 400 | 400 + error | (actual) | ✅/❌/— |\n| Integration: missing identifiers → 400 | 400 + error | (actual) | ✅/❌/— |\n\n## Score: X/10\n\n## Verdict: APPROVED / NEEDS_WORK\n\n## Feedback for next sprint\n(only if NEEDS_WORK)\n\n| Criterion | Error | File:Line | Action |\n|-----------|-------|-----------|--------|\n\n## Notes\n```\n\nScore guidelines:\n- 10: All criteria pass (or integration gaps are infrastructure-blocked, not code issues)\n- 8-9: Phase A all pass, integration gaps blocked by infrastructure (acceptable)\n- 4-7: Phase A failures\n- 1-3: Fundamental issues\n\n**IMPORTANT**: Write the eval file to `/Users/riccardocaranfil/bitrefill/minipanel-blank-night-2/features/F5-eval-1.md`\n\nIf you write the integration test file, write it to `/Users/riccardocaranfil/bitrefill/minipanel-blank-night-2/src/app/api/events/__tests__/route.integration.test.ts`\n\nCheck the AGENTS.md / CLAUDE.md for any special instructions before